<HEADLINE> Micron May Buy NETLimited Inc. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NAMPA, Idaho (AP) -- Micron Electronics Inc. has made an offer to  
purchase one of the nation's fastest growing providers of Internet 
web hosting services for small and medium businesses. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nampa-based personal computer manufacturer did not disclose  
terms of its offer to acquire the outstanding shares in NETLimited 
Inc., which has been operating out of Los Angeles as HostPro. 
Micron said only that if a deal is struck it will be finalized by 
the end of July. 
</P>
<P>
	Micron Chairman Joel Kocher said the initiative is part of the  
company's campaign to become a full-service provider of Internet, 
networking and hardware services for small and medium-sized 
businesses. 
</P>
<P>
	And HostPro co-founder Marc Afshar suggested that the resources  
Micron offers would enable his company to become the market leader. 

  	   	
</P>
