<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Fireworks King Falls in East River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- So how does one celebrate yet another  
spectacular Independence Day fireworks show? 
</P>
<P>
	If you're Felix Grucci Jr. of the Grucci fireworks family, you  
get yourself fished out of the East River. 
</P>
<P>
	After a round of congratulations and hugging, Grucci, 46, backed  
up and fell through a rotted section of a city pier Sunday night. 
Grucci plunged into the river and clung to a piling for a few 
minutes until rescued by a firefighter and an off-duty police 
officer. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was a frightening experience,'' said Grucci, who was taken  
to a hospital for a checkup. ``I went to get a tetanus shot to make 
sure I have no exotic diseases from the East River.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
