<CATEGORY> international </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Pope Begins Italian Alps Vacation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *AP Photo AOS101    	
</P>
<P>
	LES COMBES, Italy (AP) -- Pope John Paul II started a two-week  
vacation Wednesday in the Italian Alps near the French border, 
heading to a chalet with a view of Mont Blanc. 
</P>
<P>
	The 79-year-old John Paul will interrupt his rest for two public  
appearances, reciting prayers for the faithful on each Sunday that 
falls during his holiday, which ends July 20. 
</P>
<P>
	The AGI news agency reported that while being driven to his  
chalet, the pope spotted four nuns along the route, tapped on the 
car window and made the car stop so he could say hello to them. 
</P>
<P>
	Many of the local people are French-speaking, and John Paul  
greeted a crowd of about 100 people where his helicopter landed by 
thanking them in French for their welcome. 
</P>
<P>
	Children presented him with bouquets of flowers and typical  
products of the Valle d'Aosta area, including honey and homemade 
jams. 
</P>
<P>
	John Paul, an avid hiker in his youth in Poland and in the first  
years of his papacy before illness and accidents took their toll, 
is expected to take brief strolls and spend time outdoors in prayer 
and meditation. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
