<HEADLINE> Bonds Better, But Doesn't Start </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Barry Bonds' injured groin was better Wednesday  
but the San Francisco Giants star did not start against the San 
Diego Padres. 
</P>
<P>
	Bonds took batting practice and said he'd be available for  
emergency pinch-hitting duty. 
</P>
<P>
	``It doesn't bother me hitting,'' said Bonds, who pulled his  
right groin running out a grounder in the third inning of Tuesday 
night's 10-9 victory. ``It would have to be in a situation where I 
don't have to run.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Bonds ran on a treadmill for about five minutes and went through  
other exercises before the game. 
</P>
<P>
	``I feel fine,'' Bonds said. ``I've never pulled a groin in my  
life. It's a joke. I can't believe it.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Giants are off Thursday before beginning a three-game home  
series against St. Louis. 
</P>
<P>
	Bonds missed 47 games earlier this season after undergoing  
surgery on his left elbow. 
</P>
<P>
	The Giants said closer Robb Nen will undergo an MRI Thursday on  
his right elbow to determine the treatment he'll receive during the 
All-Star break. Nen aggravated his elbow when a callous on his 
right thumb made him change his grip. Nen was named to the All-Star 
team but won't play because of the injury. 
</P>
<P>
	``My thing is to get it right,'' said Nen, tied for the NL lead  
with 21 saves. ``I'm gearing up for the second half.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Manager Dusty Baker said Nen wouldn't be available Wednesday  
night. 
  	   	
</P>
