<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Williams Sisters Make Fed Cup Debut </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WHITE PLAINS, N.Y. (AP) -- Sisters Venus and Serena Williams will  
make their Fed Cup debut when the United States plays Italy in a 
second-round match later this month. 
</P>
<P>
	U.S. Fed Cup Captain Billie Jean King on Wednesday selected the  
Williams sisters along with Monica Seles and Mary Joe Fernandez to 
face the Italians on July 24-25 in Ancona, Italy. 
</P>
<P>
	Both Venus and Serena Williams had been invited to play Fed Cup  
previously, but had declined the offer until now. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's great to have a team composed of veterans and rookies.  
... I couldn't ask for better rookies than Venus and Serena, and I 
am glad that they are playing Fed Cup for the United States,'' King 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	The United States has won the Fed Cup 15 times, more than any  
other country, since the event began in 1963. The Americans have a 
7-0 record against Italy, which has never won the Fed Cup. 
</P>
<P>
	Venus Williams is ranked No. 4 in the world, while Serena is  
ranked 12th. 
</P>
<P>
	Seles, ranked fifth, is undefeated in Fed Cup play with a 10-0  
singles mark and a 1-0 doubles record. 
</P>
<P>
	Fernandez made her Fed Cup debut in 1991 and has a 12-8 record  
in singles and 4-2 in doubles. She is currently ranked 33rd in the 
world. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
