<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Sony To Exit US Mobile Phone Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- Japanese electronics giant Sony Corp. plans to stop  
selling mobile phones in North America, the company said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Sony will withdraw from the American market to concentrate its  
resources on development of next-generation digital mobile phones, 
the company said in a statement. 
</P>
<P>
	Sony was a latecomer to the American mobile phone market,  
starting there in 1995. 
</P>
<P>
	The company will try to find jobs at other U.S. subsidiaries for  
the 200 employees now working in the mobile phone unit, it said. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
