<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Comets 80, Lynx 54 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOUSTON (AP) -- Sheryl Swoopes, the leading vote-getter for the  
WNBA All-Star Game, and Western Conference starters Cynthia Cooper 
and Tina Thompson combined for 50 points Tuesday night as Houston 
beat the Minnesota Lynx 80-54. 
</P>
<P>
	Cooper had 21 points and nine assists, one shy of her career  
high; Swoopes added 15 points; and Thompson, who didn't get on the 
board until after the half, added 14 and nine rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
	Sonja Henning also had 14 points for Houston, which was  
31-for-58 (53.4 percent). Minnesota shot only 31 percent 
(22-for-71) and missed 19 of 25 3-pointers. 
</P>
<P>
	After making their first shot, the Lynx missed the next 11 as  
Houston took control early. A 10-2 run gave Houston a 20-7 lead 
with 7:46 left in the half. 
</P>
<P>
	Cooper scored 14 in the first half and Henning 10 as the Comets  
took a 36-22 lead into the break. Houston shot 48.3 percent 
(14-for-29) from the floor compared to just 22.2 (8-for-36) for the 
Lynx in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
	Adia Barnes led Minnesota with nine points.  
</P>
<P>
	Houston used a 24-5 run to build its biggest lead after  
Minnesota closed to 46-32. 
</P>
<P>
	Cooper, the league's leading scorer at 23.4 points a game,  
hasn't reached her average in the last five games, but the Comets 
have won four in a row and the last three at home. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
