<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Dow Closes at New High 11,187.36  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks bobbed and weaved into record territory  
today as the beginning of the second-quarter earnings-report season 
injected uncertainty into the market. After trading in a narrow 
range for much of the session, the Dow Jones industrial average 
closed up 52.24 at 11,187.36. The blue-chip index topped its 
previous record of 11,139.24, set last Friday. The Standard &AMP; 
Poor's 500 and Nasdaq composite index also set records, posting 
modest gains after shifting in and out of positive territory 
throughout the session. The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 rose 7.74 to 
1,395.86, and the Nasdaq composite index rose 6.18 to 2,742.96. 

</P>
<P>
	Financial Figures  
</P>
