<HEADLINE>  Swoopes Leads WNBA All-Star Vote </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Sheryl Swoopes was the top vote-getter in the  
final fan balloting for the WNBA All-Star game in New York on July 
14. 
</P>
<P>
	She is among three Houston Comets voted to the starting lineup  
for the Western Conference. Three players from the New York Liberty 
were voted to the Eastern Conference starting lineup. 
</P>
<P>
	In figures released Tuesday by the WNBA, Swoopes received 84,632  
votes, while Comets teammates guard Cynthia Cooper had 80,806 and 
Tina Thompson had 58,286. The other Western Conference starters are 
Los Angles center Lisa Leslie (66,219) and Phoenix guard Michele 
Timms (39,171). 
</P>
<P>
	The three Liberty starters are center Kym Hampton (55,432),  
guard Teresa Weatherspoon (49,332) and forward Rebecca Lobo 
(38,779). The other starters are rookie forward Chamique Holdsclaw 
(62,841) and guard Nikki McCray (38,051). 
</P>
<P>
	Lobo is out for the season with a knee injury. East coach Linda  
Hill-McDonald of the Cleveland Rockers will choose a replacement 
starter among the reserves, who will be announced on Thursday. 
Houston's Van Chancellor coaches the West. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
