<HEADLINE> People's Princess Wins in Calif. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Odds-on favorite People's Princess  
moved ahead of pacesetter Shifty Hussey early in the stretch, then 
held off Speaking Of Time to win Wednesday's $49,980 feature at 
Hollywood Park. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Chris McCarron and carrying 115 pounds, People's  
Princess finished one length in front of Speaking Of Time, with 
Shifty Hussey hanging on for third, another 3 1/2 lengths behind. 
</P>
<P>
	People's Princess, a lightly raced 3-year-old, was clocked in  
1:43 1-5 in the 1 1-16-mile race for fillies and mares aged 3 and 
up. 
</P>
<P>
	The winner paid $3.80, $2.80 and $2.40. Speaking Of Time, ridden  
by Matt Garcia, was worth $5.40 and $3.80. The show payoff on 
Shifty Hussey, ridden by Alex Solis, was $4.60. 
</P>
<P>
	People's Princess, a Kentucky-bred daughter of Meadowlake who  
was sold for $800,000 as a yearling, has won two of four career 
starts. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
