<HEADLINE> Jack Klugman Sued Over Ranch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TEMECULA, Calif. (AP) -- Jack Klugman is being sued over a horse  
ranch he sold two years ago. 
</P>
<P>
	Ennio and Darlene Racinelli paid $3 million for the ranch. They  
filed suit last year, claiming the actor and a real estate agent 
failed to disclose more than 30 problems that will cost more than 
$100,000 to repair. 
</P>
<P>
	The Racinellis said flaws included leaks in the roof and pool,  
damaged floors, plumbing and septic problems, and broken faucets, 
refrigerator and spa. 
</P>
<P>
	Klugman's attorney, Michael Hesse, said Klugman did nothing  
wrong. A real estate agent who helped close the deal said he did 
not know of any of defects before the 40-acre property changed 
hands. 
</P>
<P>
	State law requires a seller to notify the buyer of such defects  
before purchase -- if the seller is aware of them. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
