<HEADLINE> Wrestler Lawler Runs for Mayor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) -- Jerry ``The King'' Lawler, who once  
slapped Andy Kaufman on television, is running for mayor. 
</P>
<P>
	Lawler, now a World Wrestling Federation commentator, said  
Tuesday ``literally thousands of people in Memphis'' have urged him 
to run in the Oct. 7 race. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think they're looking at me as someone who's certainly not a  
politician but a lifelong resident of Memphis and as someone who 
has a love of this city,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Lawler, 49, gained national notoriety in 1982 by slapping  
comedian Kaufman on ``Late Night With David Letterman.'' 
</P>
<P>
	His opponents include Mayor Willie Herenton, the city's first  
elected black mayor, and City Councilman Joe Ford, brother of 
former Rep. Harold Ford Sr., D-Tenn. 
  	   	
</P>
