<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Forbes Magazine Names New President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Forbes has named an executive from American  
Express as president of its flagship magazine, a new position that 
will oversee the operating aspects of the publication. 
</P>
<P>
	As president, James S. Berrien will also head up the Forbes  
Management Conference Group, a four-year-old division that puts on 
seminars for top executives. 
</P>
<P>
	Before coming to Forbes, Berrien held several posts at American  
Express Co., including publisher of the company's Food &AMP; Wine 
magazine. Most recently, he was president of American Express' 
travelers check division. 
</P>
<P>
	Berrien will oversee the circulation, ad sales, promotion and  
marketing efforts of Forbes magazine, which had been headed up by 
different executives. In addition to the main Forbes magazine, he 
will also be responsible for its two supplements, the technology 
journal Forbes ASAP and the lifestyle quarterly Forbes FYI. 
</P>
<P>
	In addition to its main magazine titles, Forbes has expanded in  
recent years into online media and book publishing. It also 
publishes American Heritage magazine. 
</P>
<P>
	In announcing the appointment Wednesday, Forbes' chief operating  
officer Timothy C. Forbes said: ``Forbes has grown from an 
organization centered largely on one publication into a company 
with multiple businesses. The appointment of Jim Berrien fortifies 
and deepens the management team of our flagship division -- Forbes 
magazine -- as well as that of our conference group.'' 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
