<HEADLINE> AP Corrects Cellular Rates Story </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The Associated Press reported erroneously in a  
July 6 story and accompanying graphic that the wireless phone 
company Sprint PCS charges for calls that are unanswered. Sprint 
PCS does not charge for such calls. 
  	   	
</P>
