<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Hollywood Wins India Cable Fight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW DELHI, India (AP) -- American film companies won a court  
battle in India today when judicial officials blocked India's two 
largest cable television networks from illegally showing top 
Hollywood films, a domestic news agency said. 
</P>
<P>
	The production houses, including Twentieth Century Fox, Columbia  
Pictures, Time Warner Entertainment and Disney Enterprises, jointly 
petitioned the New Delhi High Court accusing Siti Cable and In 
Cable and their distributors of illegally copying and broadcasting 
their films. 
</P>
<P>
	Other companies joining the lawsuit included Paramount Pictures,  
Metro-Goldwyn Mayer Studios, Tristar Pictures, Universal City 
Studios and Lucasfilm. 
</P>
<P>
	The court ordered Indian police to stop the cable networks from  
broadcasting the feature films without the permission of the 
American companies, Press Trust of India news agency said. 
</P>
<P>
	The Americans said the Indian networks recently showed  
``Speed,'' ``The Mask of Zorro,'' ``Wag the Dog,'' ``As Good As it 
Gets'' and ``City of Angels'' without permission. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
