<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Canadian Co. to Acquire Snyder </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Snyder Drug Stores Inc. is being sold to The  
Katz Group, which has drugstore chain holdings throughout Canada. 
</P>
<P>
	Terms of the sale, which requires regulatory approval, were not  
disclosed. The sale is expected to close in early October. 
</P>
<P>
	Snyder Drug, based in Minneapolis, operates 141 company-owned  
and independent drug stores in six states. Founded in 1928, Snyder 
is the largest retail drug store chain in the Twin Cities and 
employs 1,600 people in Minnesota. 
</P>
<P>
	The Katz Group, based in Edmonton, Alberta, is one of Canada's  
leading drug store operators with annual revenue exceeding $547 
million. The company operates more than 300 units in five Canadian 
provinces under the Pharma Plus Drug Mart, Rexall Drug Store and 
The Medicine Shoppe Pharmacy banners. 
</P>
<P>
	Snyder -- which has stores in Illionis, Iowa, Michigan,  
Minnesota, South Dakota and Wisconsin -- will be Katz's first 
purchase of a U.S. drug store chain and will solidify Katz as one 
of the largest drug store chains in North America with expected 
annual revenues of more than $752 million. The stores will keep the 
Snyder name. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
