<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Racing Canceled, Outage Expected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OCEANPORT, N.J. (AP) -- Planned power outages cost Monmouth Park  
patrons a chance to view and bet on horse races from four other 
tracks Wednesday night. 
</P>
<P>
	The track decided to cancel the evening simulcasting program  
after learning that GPU Energy planned to cut power in Oceanport 
and other Monmouth County towns for up to four hours to prevent 
widespread outages. 
</P>
<P>
	``It would create a real inconvenience to our players,'' track  
spokesman Steve Schwartz said. ``It's always going to go out before 
a guy said he made a winning bet.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Evening simulcasts usually attract several hundred patrons, who  
usually bet less than $100,000, he said. Bad weather has led to 
prior cancellations. 
</P>
<P>
	Simulcast wagering at Monmouth Park is to resume Thursday night.  
</P>
<P>
	Monmouth's day program Wednesday of 10 live thoroughbred races  
and simulcasts from a half-dozen other tracks was not affected, 
Schwartz said. 
</P>
<P>
	The utility said the ``rolling outages'' were needed because it  
was straining to meet continued high demand for electricity in the 
region, even with a break in a three-day heat wave. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
