<HEADLINE> Tom Kite Pulls Out of British Open  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CARNOUSTIE, Scotland (AP) -- Former U.S. Open champion and Ryder  
Cup captain Tom Kite pulled out of next week's British Open today. 
</P>
<P>
	Kite, who will miss the tournament for the first time since  
1981, cited recent poor form as his reason. 
</P>
<P>
	Kite was captain of the Ryder Cup team which lost to the  
Europeans at Valderrama in Spain two years ago. 
</P>
<P>
	Kite, the 1992 U.S. Open champion, has never won the British  
Open. His best finish was in 1978, when he tied for second behind 
Jack Nicklaus at St. Andrews. He finished 10th at Royal Troon two 
years ago. 
</P>
<P>
	Nicklaus' son, Gary, withdrew from this weekend's final  
qualifying tournament, as did Sweden's Peter Hedblom. 
  	   	
</P>
