<HEADLINE> Fiat, Mitsubishi To Build SUV </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TURIN, Italy (AP) -- Italian automaker Fiat SpA and Japan's  
Mitsubishi Motors Corp. said Wednesday they have agreed to build a 
four-wheel-drive sport utility vehicle in Italy. 
</P>
<P>
	The agreement is the first in what Fiat in a statement indicated  
could be several deals as negotiations continue in the coming weeks 
on other joint projects. 
</P>
<P>
	Pininfarina SpA, an Italian car design and production company,  
this week began producing Mitsubishi's latest version of its Pajero 
SUV, the Pinin, which also will have an annual production target of 
30,000. 
</P>
<P>
	Production of the new Fiat-Mitsubishi SUV will begin in early  
2001 at a plant outside of Turin. Three-door and five-door versions 
will be produced with either diesel or gasoline engines. Fiat will 
provide the design while Mitsubishi will furnish the body and basic 
mechanical parts. 
</P>
<P>
	Fiat has been the subject of extensive speculation that it wants  
to form an alliance or merger with another automaker to better 
compete with larger players in the consolidating global auto 
industry. The deal announced Wednesday falls far short of such an 
alliance. 
</P>
<P>
	Mitsubishi jointly produces cars in the Netherlands with Volvo  
Cars Corp., but that relationship is under review after Ford Motor 
Co. acquired Volvo's car division in January. 


  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
