<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> New $8M Facility for Kings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SACRAMENTO (AP) -- The Sacramento Kings owners have announced  
plans to build an $8 million training facility next to Arco Arena. 
</P>
<P>
	The Maloof family, which last week took over controlling  
interest in the NBA franchise and the WNBA's Sacramento Monarchs, 
said Wednesday that the 38,500-square-foot facility will serve both 
teams. 
</P>
<P>
	The facility is scheduled for completion during the Kings'  
2000-2001 season. It will include two full-sized basketball courts, 
two locker rooms, a weight-training room, a videotape viewing room 
and offices. 
</P>
<P>
	``With this training facility, we are making an investment in  
our players and basketball staffs by providing them with the 
resources to become championship caliber contenders,'' said 
co-owner Gavin Maloof. 
</P>
<P>
	The facility also will be used for the teams' community youth  
activities. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
