<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Subaru Recalling 95,000 Vehicles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DETROIT (AP) -- Subaru of America Inc. on Tuesday recalled 95,000  
Impreza and Legacy cars for removal of front tow hooks to eliminate 
a flaw that could cause air bags to deploy unintentionally. 
</P>
<P>
	If the tow hooks come in sharp contact with curbs, dips,  
potholes, railroad crossings or similar road hazards they can cause 
the air bags to deploy, the automaker said. 
</P>
<P>
	There have been no reports of serious injuries that have  
resulted in the few cases where the unintended deployment has 
occurred, the company said. 
</P>
<P>
	The recall covers some 1994 and 1995 Imprezas and some 1995 and  
1996 Legacys, excluding Outback versions. The company said it is 
notifying owners by mail and asking them to have the tow hooks 
removed by their dealer at no charge. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
