<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Texas Executes Killer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HUNTSVILLE, Texas (AP) -- A man whose nickname for himself was  
``Evil'' was executed by injection Wednesday for killing a woman 
during a burglary of her home. 
</P>
<P>
	Tyrone Fuller, 35, was convicted of killing a 26-year-old woman  
who was stabbed 44 times, beaten, whipped with an electrical cord 
and raped. 
</P>
<P>
	A pathologist determined she likely lived for several hours  
after the 1988 attack but couldn't scream for help because one of 
the stab wounds severed her vocal chords. 
</P>
<P>
	At the time of the attack, Fuller was on parole for his second  
burglary conviction. 
</P>
<P>
	One of Fuller's accomplices received a life prison term in a  
plea bargain. Charges against a third man were dropped. 
</P>
<P>
	``Please do not mourn my death or my life. I hold no bitterness  
toward no one,'' Fuller said in his final statement. ``Just 
remember the light. I'm going to let this light shine. Remember to 
let the light shine.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
