<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Marlin's Crew Chief Fined $50,000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. (AP) -- Sterling Marlin's crew chief, Scott  
Eggleston, was fined $50,000 by NASCAR on Wednesday for making 
illegal changes to Marlin's Chevrolet before Saturday's Pepsi 400. 
</P>
<P>
	The infraction was found during an inspection before the race.  
NASCAR said Eggleston will be on probation until Oct. 20. 
</P>
<P>
	Marlin finished 12th in the race, winning $52,675.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
