<HEADLINE> Man Awarded $1M in Wis. Hazing Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OCONTO, Wis. (AP) -- A computer analyst who was spanked by his  
boss with a carpenter's level as part of a company hazing has been 
awarded $1 million by a jury. 
</P>
<P>
	Franklin Smith, 36, and his wife, were awarded the punitive  
damages for the humiliation and injuries he said he suffered at 
Phillips Getschow Co. The July 1 verdict was released Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Smith, who joined the mechanical contractor company in 1995,  
said the company's chief executive officer, Kurt Getschow, told him 
to report for a ``weighing-in ceremony'' and made him stand in the 
center of a room. 
</P>
<P>
	He then hit Smith ``with great force'' across the buttocks with  
a 4-foot-long carpenter's level. 
</P>
<P>
	Smith said the incident left him with physical injuries,  
emotional distress, embarrassment and humiliation. 
</P>
<P>
	Getschow had said he went through a similar ``spoof'' two  
decades ago and pointed out that Smith never sought treatment for 
the injuries. 
  	   	
</P>
