<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily Wednesday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *Waste Management, down 19 5/8 at 33 15/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The company expects to report earnings of 67 cents to 70 cents a  
share for the second quarter, excluding merger related costs. 
Analysts had expected Waste Management to earn as much as 79 cents 
per share. 

</P>
<P>
 *Pimco Advisors Holdings LP, up 4 5/16 at 33 7/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The bond fund manager is exploring a possible sale of all or  
part of the company, The Wall Street Journal reported. Pimco has 
held preliminary talks with German insurer Allianz AG, the 
newspaper reported. 

</P>
<P>
 *Cox Communications, up 1 7/8 at 38 7/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Cox will buy cable television systems that serve 490,000  
customers from AT&AMP;T. The deal, worth more than $2.8 billion, gives 
Cox access to consumers in much of the South and Southwest. 

</P>
<P>
 *Elan Corp., down 1 1/4 at 28 1/2    	
</P>
<P>
	The Securities and Exchange Commission raised questions about  
Elan's accounting practices in a letter sent to the company in 
January. Elan, an Irish pharmaceutical company, said it has 
resolved most issues raised by the SEC. 

</P>
<P>
 *Sterling Commerce Inc., down 9 at 26 3/4    	
</P>
<P>
	The electronic commerce services and software company will miss  
earnings forecasts for its fiscal third quarter, which ended June 
30. Sterling expects to report earnings of 38 cents to 39 cents a 
share; analysts had expected 41 cents. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *New Era of Networks, down 24 5/8 at 19 7/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The Denver software company expects to report an operating loss  
of 12 cents to 22 cents a share. Analysts had called for a profit 
of 12 cents per share. Results were hurt by sales that didn't close 
by the end of the quarter, the company said. 

</P>
<P>
 *Brass Eagle Inc., down 3 1/4 at 15 3/4    	
</P>
<P>
	The maker of products for paint-ball games expects  
second-quarter earnings of 37 cents a share, meeting analysts' 
expectations. Revenue, however, should be about $17.4 million, 
compared to $19.5 million in the year-ago quarter. 

</P>
<P>
 *Metricom Inc., up 7 5/8 at 42 3/4    	
</P>
<P>
