Thursday that Sen. James Inhofe, R-Okla., was the lone senator who 
did not vote when the Senate confirmed Lawrence Summers to be 
treasury secretary. 
</P>
<P>
	Inhofe voted ``yes.'' Sen. Daniel Inouye, D-Hawaii, did not  
vote. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
