<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Upcoming Celebrity Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays    	
</P>
<P>
	In the Spotlight: Ruben Blades  
</P>
<P>
	Singer-actor Ruben Blades is one of the stars of the upcoming  
film, ``Cradle Will Rock,'' also starring Susan Sarandon, Vanessa 
Redgrave, Joan Cusack and her brother John, Bill Murray and Emily 
Watson. 
</P>
<P>
	The period film, directed by Tim Robbins, tells the true story  
of a 1930s theater troupe in New York who risked their careers to 
perform a play about labor unrest against a background of 
anti-communist censorship. 
</P>
<P>
	Blades, who was born on July 16, 1948, starred in Paul Simon's  
short-lived Broadway musical, ``The Capeman.'' His film roles 
include ``Crossover Dreams,'' ``The Milagro Beanfield Wars'' and 
``Two Jakes.'' He won Grammys for best tropical Latin performance 
for ``La Rosa de los Vientos'' (1997) and ``Escenas'' (1987). 
</P>
<P>
	Blades was the Movimiento Papa Egoro's candidate in the 1994  
presidential elections in Panama. 
</P>
<P>
	Also in the birthday spotlight:  
</P>
<P>
	-- Comedian Bill Cosby, born July 12, 1937, is the author of a  
new book, ``Congratulations! Now What? -- A Book for Graduates'' 
(Hyperion). Cosby, who is a regular speaker at college 
commencements, has filled the book with humorous observations and 
sage advice from speeches he has given. 
</P>
<P>
	-- Actor Donald Sutherland, born July 17, 1935, is one of the  
stars of ``The Hunley,'' a made-for-cable movie airing on Turner 
Network Television. ``The Hunley'' is the story of a hand-cranked 
Confederate submarine that went down with its nine-man crew in 
February 1864 after sinking a Union blockade ship. 

</P>
<P>
	Celebrity birthdays July 11-17:  
</P>
<P>
	July 11: Actor Tab Hunter is 68. Singer Bonnie Pointer is 48.  
Actress Sela Ward (``Sisters'') is 43. Singer Peter Murphy of 
Bauhaus is 42. Singer Michael Rose of Black Uhuru is 42. Musician 
Richie Sambora of Bon Jovi is 40. Singer Suzanne Vega is 40. 
Actress Debbe Dunning (``Home Improvement'') is 33. Actor Michael 
Rosenbaum (``Zoe, Duncan, Jack and Jane'') is 27. Rapper Lil' Kim 
is 24. 
</P>
<P>
	July 12: Actor-comedian Bill Cosby is 62. Singer-musician  
Christine McVie is 56. Actress Mel Harris is 42. Musician Dan 
Murphy of Soul Asylum is 37. Actress Lisa Nicole Carson (``Ally 
McBeal'') is 30. Rapper Magoo is 26. Singer Tracie Spencer is 23. 
Actor Topher Grace (``That '70s Show'') is 21. 
</P>
<P>
	July 13: Actor Patrick Stewart is 59. Singer-musician Roger  
McGuinn of the Byrds is 57. Actor Harrison Ford is 57. 
Actor-comedian Cheech Marin is 53. Country singer Louise Mandrell 
is 45. Actor-director Cameron Crowe is 42. Singer Deborah Cox is 
26. 
</P>
<P>
	July 14: Actress Gloria Stuart (``Titanic'') is 89. Director  
Ingmar Bergman is 81. Actor Harry Dean Stanton is 73. Actor Matthew 
Fox (``Party of Five'') is 33. 
</P>
<P>
	July 15: Actor Jan-Michael Vincent is 55. Singer Linda Ronstadt  
is 53. Actress Lolita Davidovich is 38. Actor-director Forest 
Whitaker is 38. Musician Phillip Fisher of Fishbone is 32. Actor 
Scott Foley (``Felicity'') is 27. Actor Brian Austin Green 
(``Beverly Hills 90210'') is 26. 
</P>
<P>
	July 16: Actor-singer Ruben Blades is 51. Actress Phoebe Cates  
is 36. Actor-comedian Will Ferrell (``Saturday Night Live'') is 32. 
Actress Rain Pryor (``Head of the Class'') is 30. Actor Corey 
Feldman is 28. Singer-musician Ed Kowalczyk of Live is 28. 
</P>
<P>
	July 17: Actor Donald Sutherland is 64. Actress-singer Diahann  
Carroll is 64. Singer Spencer Davis of the Spencer Davis Group is 
57. Musician Terry ``Geezer'' Butler of Black Sabbath is 50. 
Actress Lucie Arnaz is 48. Actor David Hasselhoff is 47. Singer 
Phoebe Snow is 47. Singer Regina Belle is 36. Singer Guru of Gang 
Starr is 33. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
