<P>
	``It's not that I have to go there,'' Rivera said. ``I need to  
go there.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Rivera made his 32nd appearance of the season Tuesday night,  
suffering only his second blown save in 23 opportunities before 
getting credit for the win. Bobby Higginson tied it at 8 with two 
outs in the ninth with a solo homer, the first yielded by Rivera 
this season. 
</P>
<P>
	Torre said Nagy, who is 10-4, had been close to making the AL  
squad all along. 
</P>
<P>
	``He was right there in the voting,'' Torre said. ``I pretty  
much went with the manager's sheets, right down the line.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
