Italian captured his ninth career Tour de France stage victory, and 
his first this year. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was the perfect sprint,'' he said.  
</P>
<P>
	He paid tribute to his teammates on the Saeco team, such as Gian  
Matteo Fagnini and Mario Scirea, who worked mightily to get him 
into proper position for the final sprint. 
</P>
<P>
	Cipollini is ninth in the overall standings, 44 seconds behind  
Kirsipuu. 
</P>
<P>
	So far, this year's Tour has had little of the controversy that  
enveloped last year's race when a drug scandal almost scuttled the 
entire event. 
</P>
<P>
	Manolo Saiz, sports director of the ONCE team, who was initially  
banned from this year's Tour for involvement in the drug scandal 
but then was reinstated, said in Le Monde on Wednesday that he 
thought that ``90, if not 99, percent of the riders in this year's 
Tour de France are clean.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
