<HEADLINE> First Lady Campaign Costs Taxpayers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Hillary Clinton's Senate campaign committee  
will pick up many of the costs of her travels around New York 
State, but not all of them. 
</P>
<P>
	While the campaign committee plans to pay for her travels around  
the state as she gauges support for a Senate run, federal taxpayers 
will pick up the tab for security. Accommodations and other 
expenses for the Secret Service aides accompanying Mrs. Clinton 
would continue to be the federal government's responsibility. 
</P>
<P>
	The campaign would pay the costs of political aides accompanying  
the first lady. 
</P>
<P>
	The campaign committee also would reimburse the federal  
government for the cost of airplane tickets for Mrs. Clinton and 
her political aides when Mrs. Clinton flies to the state to 
campaign. The cost is the rate for comparable commercial airfares, 
according to federal election law. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
