<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Jenkins agrees to terms with Tigers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DETROIT (AP) -- Infielder Neil Jenkins, Detroit's third-round  
pick in the 1999 player draft, agreed to terms on a contract 
Wednesday, the team said. 
</P>
<P>
	Jenkins, 18, selected out of Dwyer High School in Jupiter, Fla.,  
was rated the second-best high school power hitter in the draft. 
</P>
<P>
	The right-hander batted .561 with 16 home runs, 45 RBIs and  
seven stolen bases last season. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
